    "body": "# What Is Answer Engine Optimization?\n\nIf you're asking this question, you're not behind \u2014 you're early. Almost nobody had heard this term two years ago, because the thing it describes didn't really exist yet.\n\n**Answer engine optimization (AEO) is the practice of making your website understandable to AI systems \u2014 like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google's AI Overviews \u2014 so they can accurately read, trust, and cite what your site offers.**\n\nThat's the one-sentence version. Here's the plain-English version underneath it.\n\n## The short history that explains why this matters\n\nFor about twenty years, getting found online meant one thing: search engine optimization, or SEO. You optimized your website so Google's crawler could find it, understand it, and rank it in a list of blue links. A person would then scan that list and click whichever one looked most useful.\n\nThat's changing. More people are now asking an AI system a question directly and getting a written answer back \u2014 no list, no clicking through ten options. Sometimes the AI mentions a source. Sometimes it doesn't. Either way, your website isn't competing to be *ranked* anymore. It's competing to be *understood well enough to be worth mentioning at all.*\n\nThat shift is what AEO responds to.\n\n## How AEO is different from SEO\n\nSEO and AEO aren't opposites \u2014 they overlap a lot \u2014 but they're not the same test, either.\n\n- **SEO** is mostly about links, keywords, and signals that help a crawler decide where your page ranks in a list.\n- **AEO** is about whether an AI system can clearly understand *what your page is saying*, well enough to summarize it, trust it, and repeat it as part of an answer.\n\nA site can rank well in Google and still be functionally invisible to an AI system, if that AI system can't clearly parse what the page actually means. That's the gap AEO exists to close.\n\n## What AEO actually involves\n\nThree things, working together:\n\n1. **Making your site machine-readable** \u2014 adding structured data and AI visibility files (like llms.txt and JSON-LD) that plainly tell AI systems what your business is and what your pages contain, in a format they parse instantly instead of guessing at.\n2. **Writing content in the shape AI systems pull answers from** \u2014 direct questions and direct answers, rather than content written purely to rank in a search list.\n3. **Making sure that content is easy to find and verify as trustworthy** \u2014 through clean technical structure and, increasingly, redundant distribution (like mirroring key content to GitHub Pages).\n\nMiss any one of these and the others don't work as well on their own.\n\n## Why this is worth paying attention to now\n\nHere's the honest, non-hyped version: almost no one has done this yet. Not because it's difficult \u2014 because most site owners don't know it's a thing they should be doing. That's a real, if temporary, advantage. The same kind of advantage early SEO adopters had twenty years ago, before \"optimizing for Google\" was something every business did as a matter of course.\n\nThat window narrows every month more people learn this exists.\n\n---\n\n**Want to see the full system this fits into** \u2014 visibility files, content strategy, and technical distribution, all mapped out together? **[Read the complete guide \u2192]** (link back to guide article page and delete this)\n\n**Curious what this looks like automated, instead of pieced together by hand?** **[See how AE Optimizer sets this up for your site \u2192]** \n(links to the sales page demo)",
