    "body": "# What Is llms.txt?\n\nIf you've never heard of this file before, that's completely normal \u2014 it's brand new, and most websites don't have one yet.\n\n**llms.txt is a plain-text file that lives on your website and gives AI systems a clear, direct summary of what your site is and what's on it** \u2014 so they don't have to guess by scanning your homepage design and hoping they interpret it correctly.\n\n## A file you've probably already benefited from, just for a different audience\n\nYou may already be familiar with something called robots.txt \u2014 a small file websites have used for years to tell search engine crawlers which pages they're allowed to look at. llms.txt works on a similar principle, but for a different audience: instead of talking to search engine crawlers, it's talking directly to AI systems, and instead of just saying \"you can look here\" or \"don't look there,\" it actually explains what your site *is* \u2014 your purpose, your key pages, what questions you can answer.\n\nThink of it like handing a new visitor a one-page summary of your entire business before they even walk in the door. That's what this file does, except the \"visitor\" is an AI system trying to decide whether your site is worth reading closely and worth mentioning in an answer.\n\n## What's actually inside one\n\nAn llms.txt file is plain text \u2014 nothing fancy, nothing that requires code to read. It typically includes things like:\n\n- A short, clear description of what the website or business is\n- Links to the most important pages on the site\n- A summary of the kind of content or answers visitors can expect to find\n\nIt's short by design. The goal isn't to cram in everything \u2014 it's to give an AI system a fast, accurate orientation, the same way a good \"About\" page gives a person a fast orientation.\n\n## Why it matters right now\n\nHere's the honest reason this is worth doing: AI systems are making judgment calls, constantly, about which sites to trust and cite. A site with a clear llms.txt file is handing that judgment call an easy answer. A site without one is asking the AI system to guess \u2014 and when AI systems have to guess, they often default to sites that made it easy, even if those sites aren't objectively the best option.\n\nThis doesn't replace anything else on your site. It sits quietly in the background, doing one job well.\n\n---\n\n**Want to see how this fits into the bigger picture** \u2014 alongside structured data, content strategy, and the rest of what makes a site AI-visible? **[Read the complete guide \u2192]**\n\n**Want this generated and installed on your site automatically, instead of writing it by hand?** **[See how AE Optimizer sets this up for your site \u2192]**",
