    "body": "The number on a pricing page isn't always the number you'll actually pay. A few tools in this space have pricing structures worth reading closely before you commit \u2014 here's what to watch for.\n\n## Where the Sticker Price Isn't the Real Price\n\n**Ahrefs Brand Radar**\nListed at $199/mo per engine, or $699/mo for all 6 engines. What's easy to miss: Brand Radar isn't a standalone product \u2014 it requires an active Ahrefs subscription to function, which runs $129\u2013$449/mo on its own. Add that in, and the realistic monthly total lands at $828\u2013$1,148+, roughly 4\u20136x the number that appears on the feature comparison page.\n\n**Prompt and credit-based tools generally**\nSeveral tools on the market \u2014 Profound, SE Visible, Peec AI, Otterly.AI, Scrunch AI, AthenaHQ \u2014 price their tiers around a fixed number of prompts or credits per month (anywhere from 100 to 3,600, depending on the tool and tier). This isn't hidden exactly, but it's easy to underestimate: if your usage exceeds the included prompt volume, you're either capped, charged overage, or pushed into the next tier up. Worth checking each tool's overage policy specifically before assuming the advertised price is your actual monthly cost.\n\n**Enterprise tiers, generally**\nProfound, Goodie AI, Peec AI, Otterly.AI, Scrunch AI, and AthenaHQ all list their top tier simply as \"custom\" or \"Enterprise \u2014 contact us.\" That's not a hidden cost so much as an unlisted one \u2014 Profound's enterprise tier alone is known to run $2,000\u2013$5,000+/mo, and there's no way to know where you'll land on that range without a sales conversation.\n\n**Evertune**\nStarts at $3,000+/mo with no published ceiling \u2014 the least transparent pricing structure on this list, though it does cover the widest range of AI engines (9+) of anything currently available.\n\n## What This Category of Tool Is Actually Priced Around\n\nAlmost universally, the monthly monitoring tools are priced around *volume of tracking* \u2014 number of prompts, engines, brands, or credits \u2014 which means your actual bill scales with how much visibility data you want, not with any fixed deliverable. That's a reasonable model for an ongoing analytics product. It's a much harder one to budget for accurately before you've used it for a month or two.\n\n## The Alternative: A Fixed, One-Time Cost\n\nIf avoiding scaling or hidden costs matters to you, the implementation-focused tools in this category are priced differently \u2014 a single, fixed cost with no usage tiers, no required add-on subscription, and no \"contact us\" pricing wall:\n\n- **AE Optimizer** \u2014 $247 one-time\n- **AIO Visibility Hub** \u2014 $497 one-time\n- **AI Referrals Hub** \u2014 $1,497 one-time (built for attorneys and law firms)\n\nWhat you pay is what you pay \u2014 no prompt limits to track, no companion subscription required, no enterprise tier hidden behind a sales call.",
