    "body": "Not every business is solving the same problem at the same stage. Here's how the current AEO and AI visibility tools map to where a business actually is \u2014 from just starting out to running a large, established brand.\n\n## Solo Businesses & Small Teams (Not Yet Visible in AI Search)\n\nIf you don't know whether AI systems can even find and cite your business yet, a monitoring subscription isn't the right first purchase \u2014 there's nothing meaningful to monitor. What you need is a foundation: visibility files, structured data, and content built for how AI systems pull answers.\n\n- **AE Optimizer \u2014 $247 one-time.** The lowest-cost entry point on the market, built specifically for this stage \u2014 get the visibility files, structured data, and AI-ready FAQ content in place first.\n- **AIO Visibility Hub \u2014 $497 one-time.** A more complete implementation package for businesses wanting a fuller setup in one purchase.\n\nNeither requires an ongoing subscription, which matters most at this stage \u2014 no recurring cost while you're still establishing whether AI visibility even moves the needle for your business.\n\n## Specialized & Higher-Stakes Fields (Legal, Professional Services)\n\nSome industries carry more competition and higher client value per lead, which changes the calculus.\n\n- **AI Referrals Hub \u2014 $1,497 one-time.** Purpose-built for attorneys and law firms navigating AI-driven referral discoverability, where a single new client relationship can easily justify a higher one-time investment.\n\nIf your field is similarly high-stakes and referral-driven, a purpose-built option like this is worth the higher entry cost over a generic implementation package.\n\n## Growing Businesses Wanting Ongoing Visibility Tracking\n\nOnce the fundamentals are in place and you want to track how you're actually performing across AI engines \u2014 mentions, citations, sentiment \u2014 a monitoring subscription starts to earn its cost.\n\n- **AthenaHQ \u2014 $95/mo.** The lowest-cost entry into ongoing monitoring.\n- **SE Visible (SE Ranking) \u2014 $189\u2013$519/mo.** Scales with prompt volume and number of brands tracked, good for a growing team watching multiple properties.\n- **Otterly.AI \u2014 $189\u2013$489/mo** and **Peec AI \u2014 ~$200\u2013505/mo.** Similar mid-range monitoring options, differing mainly in prompt volume per tier.\n- **Scrunch AI \u2014 $250/mo** and **Writesonic (GEO) \u2014 $249/mo.** Comparable mid-tier options with slightly different platform coverage and reporting features.\n\n## Larger Teams & Established Brands\n\nBusinesses with multiple brands, higher tracking volume needs, or dedicated marketing teams tend to outgrow the smaller monitoring tiers.\n\n- **Goodie AI \u2014 $295\u2013$495/mo**, focused specifically on eCommerce and AI shopping visibility.\n- **Ahrefs Brand Radar \u2014 $199\u2013$699/mo** (plus a required Ahrefs subscription), useful if you're already inside the Ahrefs ecosystem for traditional SEO.\n- **Profound \u2014 $399/mo**, scaling to **$2,000\u2013$5,000+/mo** at the enterprise tier for wider engine coverage and custom reporting.\n\n## Large Enterprises & Agencies\n\nAt this scale, cost is less of a constraint than coverage and depth of reporting.\n\n- **Evertune \u2014 $3,000+/mo.** The widest AI engine coverage (9+) currently available, focused on brand perception tracking at scale.\n- **Enterprise tiers** across Profound, Goodie AI, Peec AI, Otterly.AI, Scrunch AI, and AthenaHQ \u2014 all custom-priced, typically requiring a sales conversation.\n\n## The Simple Version\n\nJust starting out and not yet visible in AI search: start with implementation (AE Optimizer, AIO Visibility Hub, or AI Referrals Hub for legal). Already visible and want to track performance: layer in a monitoring subscription that fits your prompt volume and budget. Most businesses researching this for the first time are in the first group, not the second.",
