    "slug": "what-is-an-aeo-tool",
    "title": "What Is an AEO Tool, and What Should You Actually Pay For One?",
    "description": "A plain explanation of AEO tools, AI visibility, and what's actually available in this brand-new category.",
    "body": "If you've started seeing terms like \"AI visibility,\" \"answer engine optimization,\" or \"AEO tool\" and aren't quite sure what any of it means, you're not behind \u2014 this entire category is brand new. Here's a plain explanation of what these tools actually do, followed by exactly what's available and what it costs.\n\n## What \"AI Visibility\" Actually Means\n\nMore people are getting answers directly from AI systems \u2014 ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google's AI Overviews \u2014 instead of clicking through a list of search results. Whether a business shows up in those answers depends on something different from traditional SEO: whether the AI system can clearly read, understand, and trust what that business offers.\n\n**AI visibility** is the general term for whether your business shows up in these AI-generated answers at all. **Answer engine optimization (AEO)** is the practice of actively working to improve that \u2014 through structured data, AI-readable files, and content written the way these systems pull answers from.\n\n## The Two Kinds of Tools in This Category\n\nAlmost everything currently on the market falls into one of two buckets, and it's worth understanding the difference before you spend anything:\n\n**Monitoring tools** track how often your business is already being mentioned or cited across AI engines \u2014 dashboards, prompt tracking, sentiment analysis. Useful once you have visibility worth tracking.\n\n**Implementation tools** actually build the things that make a business citable in the first place \u2014 visibility files, structured data, FAQ content in the right format. Useful before you have visibility, to create it.\n\n## Monitoring Tools \u2014 Current Pricing\n\n- **Profound** \u2014 Growth $399/mo (3 engines, 100 prompts), Enterprise $2,000\u2013$5,000+/mo\n- **Ahrefs Brand Radar** \u2014 $199/mo per engine or $699/mo for all 6, plus a required Ahrefs subscription ($129\u2013$449/mo)\n- **Goodie AI** \u2014 Starter $295/mo, Pro $495/mo, Enterprise custom (eCommerce focus)\n- **SE Visible (SE Ranking)** \u2014 $189\u2013$519/mo depending on tier\n- **Peec AI** \u2014 ~$200\u2013505/mo depending on tier\n- **Otterly.AI** \u2014 $189\u2013$489/mo depending on tier\n- **Scrunch AI** \u2014 $250/mo, Enterprise custom\n- **AthenaHQ** \u2014 $95/mo (annual plan), Enterprise custom\n- **Writesonic (GEO)** \u2014 $249/mo (Professional tier)\n- **Evertune** \u2014 starting at $3,000+/mo (9+ engines tracked)\n\n## Implementation Tools \u2014 Current Pricing\n\n- **AE Optimizer** \u2014 $247 one-time\n- **AIO Visibility Hub** \u2014 $497 one-time\n- **AI Referrals Hub** \u2014 $1,497 one-time (built for attorneys/law firms)\n\n## What You Should Actually Pay For, First\n\nIf you don't currently know whether your business shows up in AI-generated answers, start with implementation. There's no value in monitoring a signal that doesn't exist yet \u2014 you'd essentially be paying monthly to confirm you're invisible, without doing anything to change that. A one-time investment in visibility files, structured data, and AI-ready content addresses the actual root cause.\n\nOnce that foundation is in place, a monitoring tool becomes genuinely useful \u2014 you'll have real citations and mentions worth tracking, and the monthly cost buys you visibility into performance rather than just a status update on a problem you already know you have.\n\nIn short: fix the foundation before you start measuring it.",
